#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:49
#: patterns/faq/default.php:37
msgid "How do I replace this default Homepage?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:51
#: patterns/faq/default.php:39
msgid "This layout is the default Home template. To replace it with your own content, simply create a new Page, publish it, and assign it as your \"Homepage\" under Settings → Reading. Once your new Homepage is set, you should delete the front-page.php template file from the theme to prevent it from overriding your chosen page."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:58
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:48
#: patterns/faq/default.php:46
#: patterns/page/home.php:1662
msgid "Where is the classic Customizer?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:60
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:50
#: patterns/faq/default.php:48
#: patterns/page/home.php:1664
msgid "The Customizer has been retired in favor of the Site Editor (Appearance → Editor). This gives you total control over headers, footers, and page templates visually, without relying on legacy options."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:67
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:57
#: patterns/faq/default.php:55
#: patterns/page/home.php:1672
msgid "How to change the site logo?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:69
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:59
#: patterns/faq/default.php:57
#: patterns/page/home.php:1674
msgid "Access the Header template part within the Site Editor. Select the existing placeholder and replace it with a Site Logo, Image, or Inline SVG block. We recommend utilizing raw SVG for infinite scalability and dynamic color adaptation across dark mode."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-sidebar.php:76
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:66
#: patterns/faq/default.php:64
#: patterns/page/home.php:1682
msgid "How do I edit the navigation menu?"
